answers.answer: I have 26 days left and I just barely started getting baby's bag ready lol. Haven't had any bad symptoms during my pregnancy.

I have 27 days left and I'm so ready! Everything is washed just need to sterilize feeding supplies. I just need to purchase some nursing bras and shirts because all of mine are pull overs. Symptoms are just super fatigued and tired, every little task is like running a marathon and my feet are swollen. Other than that everything is great!
congrats! My feet haven't swollen yet! thank goodness lol

34 weeks tomorrow!! I'm soooo ready I'm thinking he'll be here earlier than the 23rd I had massive contractions at my appt on Wed. I was in the hospital under observation for 24hrs. I haven't washed anything yet I figure I'd do it this week. I'm going to pick out a stroller & other things I need . super hyped lol

I'm 34 weeks and having my princess in 38 days! Just had my baby shower today, got a lot of stuff! only big thing I need to get is a swing and bouncer.. will be going tomorrow to get that! Already washed all her clothes and have her bag packed. Just need to pack mine (:
congrats girls! Are yall nervous at all?
I'm super nervous. I don't have any tolerance for pain lol how about you?!
Very nervous lol not so much about the pain, just nervous all together lol
22 days left. Feb 3rd. Well I'm dilated already and always in pain. Praying my girl comes soon cause i can't take it anymore lol. Anyone else up every two hours??
me! I just cant seem to sleep through the night anymore :(

question: How are you ladies holding up? Im 33+6 tomorrow (Sunday) and I am doing ok. I feel huge and my stomach is soo heavy lol I am so ready for my princess to be here next month :)))Went to the dr at 33+3 and everything was fine with me and baby! I have gained 22lbs so far and my dr says that is wonderful, especially considering I have gestational diabetes!What are your main pregnancy symptoms right now? Have you started washing baby things and getting everything ready? Im gonna start washing everything this week and figure out what will be going to the hospital with us :)
